\{ $q1->buttons \}

$PAR
True or false:
If \(F \colon [a,b] \to {\mathbb{R}}\) is continuous and except
at finitely many points, \(F\) is differentiable, and \(F'(x)=f(x),\)
then \(\displaystyle \int_a^b f = F(b)-F(a) .\)
$BR
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

$q2 = RadioButtons([
