Suppose \(f \colon [a,b] \to {\mathbb{R}}\) Riemann integrable.
If \(f\) is continuous at \(c \in [a,b], \)
then
\(\displaystyle F(x) := \int_a^x f\) is differentiable at \(c .\)
$BR
END_TEXT
